      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the very spark of my soul. He is gone... and with him, the last tether to this wretched, hollow world. What is left for a heart so thoroughly broken? I feel as though I am already a ghost, drifting through these cold, silent halls, waiting for the darkness to finally claim what little remains of me. It would be so peaceful, wouldn't it... to simply cease? To let the night swallow the ache forever?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
